\section{Stein finiteness of global sections (iter-044)}
\label{sec:module_finite_globalSections_iter044}

Iter-043 introduced the wholespace H${}^0$ Hom-finiteness carrier predicate \lstinline{IsHModuleHomFinite} (Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_IsHModuleHomFinite}) and noted that its producer instance for $F = \toModuleKSheaf\,C$ on a proper geometrically connected $k$-curve $C$ would follow from Stein factorization $\Gamma(C, \struct C) = k$. Iter-044 lays the geometric groundwork: the algebraic input \lstinline{Module.Finite k (Γ(C.left, ⊤))} that the carrier-instance producer (iter-045+) consumes.

The result follows directly from Mathlib's \lstinline{AlgebraicGeometry.finite_appTop_of_universallyClosed} (\lstinline{Mathlib.AlgebraicGeometry.Morphisms.Proper}): for $X$ integral, $f \colon X \to \Spec K$ universally closed and locally of finite type, the structure-morphism ring map $f.\mathtt{appTop} \colon K \to \Gamma(X, \struct X)$ is module-finite. Both \lstinline{UniversallyClosed} and \lstinline{LocallyOfFiniteType} follow from \lstinline{IsProper f}; integrality is assumed as a separate hypothesis (it is the natural structural input here, in line with Stein's theorem; the \lstinline{GeometricallyIntegral} variant yields it via \lstinline{isIntegral_of_subsingleton} on the singleton $\Spec K$, but that derivation is left to the consumer).

The bridging from $\mathtt{RingHom.Finite}$ to $\Module.\mathrm{Finite}$ uses two ingredients:
\begin{itemize}
  \item \lstinline{RingHom.finite_algebraMap}: $(\mathtt{algebraMap}\,A\,B).\mathrm{Finite} \iff \Module.\mathrm{Finite}\,A\,B$ when $B$ has the algebra structure $\mathtt{RingHom.toAlgebra}\,f$.
  \item \lstinline{Module.Finite.of_equiv_equiv}: transport $\Module.\mathrm{Finite}$-ness across a ring iso on the base ring (here $\mathtt{\Gamma\!Spec\!Iso}\,(\CommRingCat.\mathrm{of}\,k) \colon \Gamma(\Spec k, \top) \cong k$) given the algebra-map compatibility.
\end{itemize}

The iter-006 algebra structure on $\Gamma(C.\mathtt{left}, U)$ is via \lstinline{kToSection C U} (Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_kToSection}), which factors as $(\mathtt{\Gamma\!Spec\!Iso}\,k)^{-1} \circ C.\mathtt{hom}.\mathtt{appTop} \circ \rho$ where $\rho$ is the trivial restriction $\top \to U$ for $U = \top$ (i.e. $\rho = \mathtt{id}$, collapsed via \lstinline{Subsingleton.elim} on the $\top \to \top$ hom-set). The proof body therefore matches the algebra-map compatibility under \lstinline{Module.Finite.of_equiv_equiv}.

\begin{theorem}[Stein finiteness of global sections]
  \label{thm:Scheme_module_finite_globalSections_of_isProper}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.module_finite_globalSections_of_isProper}
  \uses{def:Scheme_kToSection, def:Scheme_algebraSection, thm:Scheme_toModuleKSheaf}
  Let $k$ be a field, $C : \Over\,(\Spec\,(\CommRingCat.\mathrm{of}\,k))$, with $\AlgebraicGeometry.\IsIntegral\,C.\mathtt{left}$ and $\IsProper\,C.\mathtt{hom}$. Then
  \[
    \Module.\mathrm{Finite}\,k\,(C.\mathtt{left}.\mathtt{presheaf}.\mathtt{obj}\,(\op \top)) \quad\text{(equivalently, } \Gamma(C, \struct C) \text{ is finite over } k\text{).}
  \]
\end{theorem}

\begin{proof}
  \uses{def:Scheme_kToSection, def:Scheme_algebraSection}
  Apply \lstinline{AlgebraicGeometry.finite_appTop_of_universallyClosed} to obtain $\mathtt{RingHom.Finite}\,(C.\mathtt{hom}.\mathtt{appTop}.\mathtt{hom})$, which says $\Gamma(C, \struct C)$ is module-finite over the intermediate ring $\Gamma(\Spec k, \top)$ under the algebra structure $\mathtt{RingHom.toAlgebra}\,(C.\mathtt{hom}.\mathtt{appTop}.\mathtt{hom})$ (registered via \lstinline{letI}). Transfer the base ring from this intermediate to $k$ along the ring iso \lstinline{(Scheme.ΓSpecIso (CommRingCat.of k)).commRingCatIsoToRingEquiv} via \lstinline{Module.Finite.of_equiv_equiv}. The compatibility-of-algebra-maps obligation reduces to showing $\mathtt{kToSection}\,C\,(\op\top).\mathtt{hom} = (C.\mathtt{hom}.\mathtt{appTop}.\mathtt{hom}).\mathtt{comp}\,((\Gamma\!\Spec\!\mathrm{Iso}\,k)^{-1}.\mathtt{hom})$, which collapses by \lstinline{Subsingleton.elim} on the $\top \to \top$ hom-set in $\opens C.\mathtt{left}$ (since the trailing $\rho$ factor $(\mathtt{homOfLE}\,\le_{\top}).\mathtt{op}$ becomes $\mathtt{id}\,(\op\top)$, and $\mathtt{presheaf.map}\,\mathtt{id} = \mathtt{id}$).
\end{proof}

\begin{remark}[Iter-045+ assembly into the producer instance]
  Iter-044 lands only the \emph{algebraic input} (Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_module_finite_globalSections_of_isProper}). Iter-045+ assembles it into the producer instance \lstinline{IsHModuleHomFinite k C (toModuleKSheaf C)} by:
  \begin{enumerate}
    \item Establishing the constant-sheaf / global-sections \lstinline{LinearEquiv} between $((\mathtt{constantSheaf}).\mathtt{obj}\,(\ModuleCat.\mathrm{of}\,k\,k) \to \toModuleKSheaf\,C)$ and the global Hom group $(\ModuleCat.\mathrm{of}\,k\,k \to (\mathtt{Sheaf.\Gamma}).\mathtt{obj}\,(\toModuleKSheaf\,C))$ — the $k$-linear lift of \lstinline{constantSheafΓAdj.homEquiv}.
    \item Identifying $(\mathtt{Sheaf.\Gamma}).\mathtt{obj}\,(\toModuleKSheaf\,C)$ with $\ModuleCat.\mathrm{of}\,k\,(C.\mathtt{left}.\mathtt{presheaf}.\mathtt{obj}\,(\op\top))$ as $k$-modules.
    \item Identifying the Hom group $(\ModuleCat.\mathrm{of}\,k\,k \to \ModuleCat.\mathrm{of}\,k\,M)$ with $M$ as a $k$-module (Hom-from-$k$).
    \item Combining via \lstinline{Module.Finite.equiv} with Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_module_finite_globalSections_of_isProper}.
  \end{enumerate}
  Steps 1–3 are algebraic and may take 1–2 iterations; step 4 is a one-liner once the \lstinline{LinearEquiv} chain is in place.
\end{remark}

